meta {
  name: GET vehicle maintenance (v3)
  type: http
  seq: 24
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/api/v3/vehicle-maintenance/vehicles/{{vin}}
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  Maintenance / service-interval data — odometer + due-in-km +
  due-in-days for both inspection and oil service.

  Response shape (verified myskoda/models/maintenance.py):
    {"maintenanceReport": {
       "mileageInKm": <int>,
       "inspectionDueInKm": <int>,
       "inspectionDueInDays": <int>,
       "oilServiceDueInKm": <int>,
       "oilServiceDueInDays": <int>
     }}
  Some firmwares omit the ``maintenanceReport`` wrapper — we fall
  back to reading the fields off the root object.

  Drives: sensor.<vin>_odometer_km, _service_km, _service_due_at,
  _oil_service_km, _oil_service_at, plus the v1.11.0 (#91) raw
  day-count sensors (_service_due_in_days, _oil_service_due_in_days).

  Implementation: gathered in SkodaClient.get_status() at
  custom_components/vag_connect/cariad/api/skoda.py:156; parsed at
  the maintenance branch around line 374.
}
